    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>$$ \\text { Given : Vertices of rectangle }=(-1-j),(3-j),(3+j) \\text { and }(-1+j) $$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mh617y8a/61189bda-47ea-469d-8b5e-5c40c42f17f2/8f2be6a0-b17e-11f0-9ec5-a735814724b3/file-jaoe38c1mh617y8b.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mh617y8a/61189bda-47ea-469d-8b5e-5c40c42f17f2/8f2be6a0-b17e-11f0-9ec5-a735814724b3/file-jaoe38c1mh617y8b.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE EE 2021 Engineering Mathematics - Complex Variable Question 1 English Explanation\">Poles $=0,0,4$</p>\n<p>$z=0$ lie inside contour and $z=4$ lie outside of contour.</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{array}{ll}  &amp; R=\\frac{1}{(n-1)!} \\frac{d^{n-1}}{d z^{n-1}}\\left(z-z_0\\right)^n f(z) \\\\ &amp; R=\\frac{1}{(2-1)!} \\frac{d}{d z} z^2 \\frac{1}{z^2(z-4)} \\\\ &amp; R=1 \\times \\frac{d}{d z} \\frac{1}{(z-4)} \\\\ &amp; R=\\frac{-1}{(z-4)^2}=\\frac{-1}{16} \\\\ \\therefore &amp; \\oint_C \\frac{d z}{z^2(z-4)}=2 \\pi i\\left(\\frac{-1}{16}\\right)=\\frac{-j \\pi}{8} \\end{array} $$</p>\n<p>Hence, the correct option is (C).</p>",
